#5
with open("cool_dogs.txt", "a") as cool_dogs_file:
  cool_dogs_file.write("Air Buddy\n")  
  answer = cool_dogs_file.read()
  print(answer)

THIS PRODUCES AN ERROR, because the file has to be in read mode to read it. If its in append mode you cannot read the file.
Correct version:
with open("cool_dogs.txt", "a") as cool_dogs_file:
  cool_dogs_file.write("Air Buddy\n")  

with open("cool_dogs.txt", "r") as answer:
  print(answer.read())
 
